ish <i>gylde</i> ‘golden’ (perhaps used here to denote a sandy hill) + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."],"variants":[{"name":"Gilford","meanings":["English: variant of   Guilford  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs William de Guilford was born about 1304, in Rolvenden, Kent, England, United Kingdom. She married William Guildford in 1326, in Rolvenden, Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1304–":"umbes 1304–Surnud","1300–1388":"1300–1388","1331–Male":"1331–Surnud","1304–Female":"1304–Surnud","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1388":"1388","1300":"1300","about 1304":"umbes 1304","1331":"1331","Benenden, Kent, England":"Benenden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rolvenden, , Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, England"},"fi":{"about 1304–":"noin 1304–Kuollut","1300–1388":"1300–1388","1331–Male":"1331–Kuollut","1304–Female":"1304–Kuollut","1326":"1326","1304":"1304","1388":"1388","1300":"1300","about 1304":"noin 1304","1331":"1331","Benenden, Kent, England":"Benenden, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Rolvenden, , Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Rolvenden, Kent, England":"Rolvenden, Kent, En